-- Treasury’s Wolin Sees No Evidence Dodd-Frank Doing Harm
-- B y   I a n   K a t z   a n d   M e e r a   L o u i s
-- 2012-03-02T13:54:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-02/treasury-s-wolin-sees-no-evidence-dodd-frank-doing-harm-1-.html
U.S. Deputy Treasury Secretary Neal Wolin said there’s no evidence that the Dodd-Frank financial
overhaul law has had any “negative effect” on the financial
system.  Wolin, in an interview with CNBC today, also said the costs
of implementing Dodd-Frank are a “pittance” compared with the
costs the country had to endure during the financial crisis.  “I think that there is no evidence frankly that the Dodd-
Frank legislation or the bits and pieces that are being
implemented as we go forward have had any negative effect on our
financial system,” Wolin said. “People are having their
ability to express their perspectives and those perspectives
will be factored in.”  “We should be attentive to the costs of compliance,”
Wolin said. “The real question to ask is ‘what are the costs
relative to not having these reforms?'''  To contact the reporter on this story:
